description:
In this lecture, Dan Wilson continues his study of typology by looking at how Revelation echoes Old Testament prophecies concerning God's judgment. Far from being a frightening, humiliating, or degrading event where we stand in shame before God in the presence of all our sins, the judgment is truly good news, great news—the best news! Dan Wilson traces the theme of judgment from Genesis to Revelation, examining our future in the light of the events of the past and the promises of God. In its proper context, the judgment becomes the event most anticipated by the children of God.
Watch the complete series:  http://amazingdiscoveries.tv/c/167/Complete_Restoration/
